    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="CH1a0941-start">
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:30:52.878+09:00">He found the confusion of relations between words and realities unacceptable.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T00:40:15.792+09:00">he produced an essay on "preserving the whiteness".</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:26:50.015+09:00">and argued for the preservation of whiteness,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:41:03.442+09:00">claiming that a white horse is to be deemed not to be a horse.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:41:13.556+09:00">As for "a white horse is to be deemed not to be a horse",</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:41:32.118+09:00">when one mentions "white",</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:29:12.41+09:00">that is that by which one names a colour,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:41:45.18+09:00">and when one mentions "horse",</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T21:07:17.438+09:00">that is that by which one names a shape.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:32:23.782+09:00">A colour is not a shape,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T01:01:04.268+09:00">and a shape is not a colour.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:32:32.683+09:00">When one mentions the colour,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:42:22.717+09:00">then the shape should not be brought in;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:33:02.101+09:00">and when one mentions a shape,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T21:33:30.409+09:00">then the colour should not be made to follow along.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T21:35:46.322+09:00">Now to combine these two (colour and shape) and to deem them to be one thing</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T01:12:27.659+09:00">is wrong.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:51:05.269+09:00">it is not there,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:51:17.98+09:00">but there is a black-colour horse instead.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T01:07:28.372+09:00">Thus it is not appropriate to respond that there is a white horse.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:04:44.464+09:00">And if it is not appropriate to respond that there is a white horse,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T21:45:38.348+09:00">then "the horse" one is seeking is not there,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:08:45.841+09:00">and if it is not there, then in point of fact a white horse is not a horse.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:52:20.215+09:00">It is as if, when you look for a white horse in the stable,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T21:49:43.777+09:00">Gōngsūn Lóng wished to further develop this kind of argument</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T21:50:56.751+09:00">in order to straighten out (the relation between) names and realities</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:08:27.751+09:00">Gōngsūn Lóng was a disputer from the Six States Period.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:39:39.912+09:00">Basing himself on those talents in which he excelled,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T21:26:28.089+09:00">He made use of things which he chose for comparison/as examples,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:10:33.472+09:00">When Lóng and Kǒng Chuān met in the home of Lord Píngyuán of Zhào,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:11:59.744+09:00">Chuān said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:14:10.186+09:00">"I have heard for a long time about your high-minded sense of justice,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:17:22.481+09:00">and I have long hoped to become your disciple.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:14:53.452+09:00">However I disagree when you believe that a white horse  is not a horses, that is all.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:24:47.725+09:00">I beg you to discard this proposition,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:27:11.416+09:00">then I shall beg to become your disciple."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:27:20.741+09:00">Lóng said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:32:55.188+09:00">"Sir, your words are inconsistent.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:28:52.765+09:00">The reason why I count as famous</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:29:17.187+09:00">is because of my essay on the white horse, that is all.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:17:26.201+09:00">Supposing now that I discard this,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:29:53.298+09:00">then I shall have nothing to teach in this regard.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:18:18.719+09:00">Moreover, when one wishes to take someone as a teacher,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:30:57.39+09:00">that is because one's wisdom and learning is less than his.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:19:28.112+09:00">Supposing not that I discard this doctrine,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:31:56.232+09:00">this would be a case of first teaching someone a lesson and then taking him as a teacher.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:20:16.298+09:00">Now to teach someone a lesson bofore taking him as a teacher,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:32:43.414+09:00">that is inconsistent.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:33:24.502+09:00">Moreoever "A white horse is not a horse"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:34:00.119+09:00">is exactly what Confucius maintains.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:22:11.398+09:00">I am told that the King of Chǔ stretched the Fánruò bow,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:36:40.208+09:00">charged it with the Never Return arrow</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:39:00.104+09:00">and went on to shoot a dragon and a rhinoceros in Yúnmèng Park,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:38:53.895+09:00">whereupon he lost his bow.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:39:35.927+09:00">An attendant asked permission to find the bow,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:39:39.948+09:00">but the King said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:48:49.277+09:00">"Don't!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:33:35.299+09:00">The King of Chǔ has lost the bow,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:49:25.957+09:00">and a man of Chǔ will find it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:49:53.096+09:00">Why go ahead and look for it?"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.33" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:33:50.266+09:00">When Confucius learnt about this, he said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:36:13.017+09:00">"The King of Chu was possessed of human-heartedness and righteousness, but he is not yet fully accomplished.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.35" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:36:52.473+09:00">He should surely just have said 'A person has lost the bow, and a person will find it.'</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.36" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T16:53:48.356+09:00">No need for any Chǔ."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.37" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:37:15.23+09:00">In this way,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.38" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T17:26:53.288+09:00">Confucius maintained a distinction between "a man of Chǔ" and what is called "a man".</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.39" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T17:27:31.954+09:00">Now to approve of Confucius distinguishing between "a man of Chǔ" and what is called "a man"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.40" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:38:20.88+09:00">but to disapprove of me distinguishing between "a white horse" and what is called "a horse",</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T17:28:18.328+09:00">that is inconsistent.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.42" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:40:14.456+09:00">If you cultivate the doctrines of the Confucians,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-1a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:12:40.049+09:00">and to transmogrify/teach everyone. [And what follows illustrates how Gōngsūn Lóng moves from 正名 to 正名實 so as to avoid incoherence. He is thus NOT proposing what to do. But he is imposing a regime of being consistent and avoiding 誖悖.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.43" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:40:34.196+09:00">but disagree with the (intellectual) choices of Confucius,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.44" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:40:55.295+09:00">if you wish to study with me, but try to make me abandon what I teach,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.45" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T22:41:15.99+09:00">then even a hundred (Gōngsūn) Lóngs</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T21:09:36.418+09:00">will most certainly be incapable of facing up to you."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-2a.47" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T21:10:11.67+09:00">Kǒng Chuān was lost for words to respond to this.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T22:09:09.09+09:00">Gōngsūn Lóng was a retainer of the Lord Píngyuán of Zhào,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T22:09:55.152+09:00">and Kǒng Chuān was a descendant of Confucius.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:19:17.543+09:00">When Chuān and Lóng met,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T22:11:53.408+09:00">Chuān told Lóng:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:20:32.624+09:00">"Living in Lǔ,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:21:08.424+09:00">I have heard from my humble sticks</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T01:21:52.992+09:00">about your honour's intellectual prowess,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-3a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T22:19:24.797+09:00">and I have explained your conduct (to others).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-3a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:45:15.888+09:00">I have long hoped to receive your instruction,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-3a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:24:49.247+09:00">and now at last I am getting to meet you.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-3a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:25:46.816+09:00">But the one point where I cannot agree with you</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-3a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:25:58.116+09:00">is on the matter of you deeming a white horse not to be a horse.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-3a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T22:24:00.376+09:00">Please give up the study of the proposition that a white horse is not a horse,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-3a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:26:51.617+09:00">then I will beg to become your disciple."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T22:25:55.868+09:00">Gōngsūn Lóng said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T22:26:14.043+09:00">"Your words</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T22:29:01.701+09:00">My study</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T01:31:38.425+09:00">is concerned with deeming a white horse not to be a horse.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:29:34.815+09:00">If I abandon this thesis,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:29:43.021+09:00">then I have nothing to teach,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T22:31:47.825+09:00">and as for studying with me when I have nothing to teach,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-09T22:32:42.668+09:00">that is to be inconsistent.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:32:18.759+09:00">Now to (try to) teach me to disavow the thesis that a white horse is not a horse,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T01:38:30.698+09:00">But to teach someone first and then afterwards to take him on as a teacher,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:34:58.414+09:00">The way you are teaching me</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T01:14:47.75+09:00">The King of Qí said to Yīn Wén:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:43:22.953+09:00">"I am very fond of (mobile) gentlemen,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:44:13.166+09:00">but I find the state of Qí has no true gentlemen. Why is that?"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T01:16:19.942+09:00">Yīn Wén said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:44:42.573+09:00">"I hope to learn about what Your Great Majesty means by a true gentleman."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T01:17:37.231+09:00">The King of Qí was lost for words to respond with.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T01:17:50.003+09:00">Yīn Wén said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T01:18:44.379+09:00">"Suppose we had a man here</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:56:25.055+09:00">who in serving his ruler showed loyal devotion,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:56:43.263+09:00">who in serving his parents showed filial piety,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:57:05.177+09:00">who in interacting with friends showed good faith</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T01:21:55.483+09:00">and as an inhabitant of his place showed compliance.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:01:54.203+09:00">If he had these four forms of behaviour,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:03:08.469+09:00">might he rightly be called a true gentleman?"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.33" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T01:22:55.096+09:00">The King of Qí said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T01:23:03.795+09:00">"Excellent!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.35" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:05:05.876+09:00">This is truly what I mean by a true gentleman."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.36" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T01:24:07.286+09:00">Yīn Wén said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.37" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:06:12.17+09:00">"If Your Majesty found such a person,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.38" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:06:34.587+09:00">would you be willing to make him your minister?"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.39" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T01:26:41.364+09:00">The King said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.40" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:07:43.612+09:00">"Such a person is whom I wish for, but they are impossible to get."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:09:56.17+09:00">At this time,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.42" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:10:08.274+09:00">the King of Qí was fond of bravery,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.43" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:10:14.671+09:00">and so Yīn Wén said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.44" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T01:29:33.329+09:00">"Suppose that this person (of those qualities) in the open court and in the presence of many people</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.45" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:11:38.542+09:00">were humiliated but to the very end did not dare to fight back,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T01:32:08.649+09:00">would Your Majesty want to appoint him as your minister?"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.47" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T01:32:20.448+09:00">The King said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.48" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:15:27.197+09:00">"How could he be a true gentleman?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.49" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:15:47.63+09:00">To be humiliated and not to fight back,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.50" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T01:37:50.414+09:00">that is a public disgrace.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.51" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:16:01.794+09:00">And if someone is publicly disgraced,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.52" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:16:12.446+09:00">then I will not make him my minister."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.53" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:15:07.251+09:00">Yīn Wén said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.54" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:16:52.853+09:00">"Not to fight back when one is being humiliated</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.55" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:20:33.648+09:00">is not yet to fail in the four forms of behaviour that I mentioned before.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.56" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:20:45.736+09:00">Such a person has not yet failed in those four forms of behaviour,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.57" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:24:12.83+09:00">and this is precisely his qualification to be a true gentleman.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.58" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:18:45.275+09:00">And yet Your Majesty will on the one hand make him your minister</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.59" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:19:02.761+09:00">and on the other hand not make him your minister,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.60" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:25:19.033+09:00">does that mean that what you just now called a true gentleman</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.61" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:25:35.101+09:00">is in fact not a true gentleman?"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.62" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:20:06.771+09:00">The King of Qí found no words to respond to this.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.63" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:24:31.97+09:00">Yīn Wén said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.64" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:26:44.327+09:00">"Suppose there is a ruler over others</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.65" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:45:30.702+09:00">who wants to govern his state.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.66" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:29:30.359+09:00">When someone has something wrong with him,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.67" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:29:38.57+09:00">then to disapprove of him,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.68" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:30:05.057+09:00">and when there is nothing wrong with him,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.69" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:46:20.696+09:00">then also to disapprove of him;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.70" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:30:27.251+09:00">when he has an achievement,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.71" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:30:36.411+09:00">then to reward him,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.72" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:30:46.969+09:00">and when he has no achievement,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.73" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:46:58.538+09:00">then also to reward him,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.74" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:32:10.481+09:00">and then, on top of that, to resent people's being unruly,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.75" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:32:23.282+09:00">is that acceptable?"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.76" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:47:39.645+09:00">The King of Qí said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.77" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:47:51.113+09:00">"That is not acceptable."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.78" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:48:05.984+09:00">Yīn Wén said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.79" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:40:20.266+09:00">"I take the liberty to to consider that, as for the way the minor officials govern Qí,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.80" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:50:08.329+09:00">it is, for the time being, like this."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.81" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:40:54.648+09:00">The King said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.82" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:41:25.466+09:00">"As for my government of the state,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.83" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:55:44.315+09:00">supposing it is as you say,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.84" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:55:55.959+09:00">then even if people are unruly</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.85" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:56:49.794+09:00">I would not presume to resent them (for it).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.86" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:42:10.204+09:00">But I imagine things have not yet got to this point."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.87" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:57:21.259+09:00">Yīn Wén said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.88" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:57:42.729+09:00">"Having said this,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.89" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T16:58:06.704+09:00">how could I dare not to have an explanation?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.90" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:42:56.221+09:00">Your Majesty's order says:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.91" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:43:15.026+09:00">'Whoever kills someone is to die,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.92" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:43:41.161+09:00">and whoever injures someone is to suffer corporal punishment.'</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.93" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:44:30.444+09:00">There are those who fear the authority of Your Majesty's order,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.94" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:45:13.691+09:00">and, when humiliated, to the very end they will not dare to fight back.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.95" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T17:22:47.674+09:00">This is to conform completely with Your Majesty's order.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.96" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T17:22:55.832+09:00">But Your Majesty says;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.97" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:46:12.723+09:00">"When one is humiliated then not to fight back,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.98" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:47:45.804+09:00">that is shameful public humiliation."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.99" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T17:25:35.045+09:00">To call it shameful humiliation</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.100" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T17:25:48.793+09:00">is to disapprove of it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.101" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:49:55.836+09:00">Someone has done no wrong, but Your Majesty  calls that a shameful public humiliation,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.102" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T17:28:44.79+09:00">and on these grounds you remove him from the register (of public servants)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.103" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T00:50:24.073+09:00">and do not make him your minister.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.104" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T17:29:14.373+09:00">Not to make him your minister</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.105" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T02:52:16.039+09:00">is to punish him.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.106" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T02:55:36.833+09:00">This means that Your Majesty punishes someone who has committed no crime.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.107" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T02:56:04.315+09:00">Moreover, if Your Majesty deems it to be a shameful public humiliation not to presume to fight back,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.108" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T02:58:18.231+09:00">you necessarily deem it honourable to dare to fight back.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.109" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T03:03:08.296+09:00">But if deeming it honourable for someone to dare to fight back is right, and if Your Majesty considers it as right,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.110" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T03:04:42.597+09:00">then you must make him your minister.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.111" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T03:12:25.644+09:00">If you must make him your minister,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.112" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T03:12:34.419+09:00">then that is to reward him.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.113" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T03:12:54.813+09:00">But if that man has no achievements and Your Majesty rewards him,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.114" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T17:35:33.991+09:00">then the person whom Your Majesty rewards</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.115" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T17:36:03.357+09:00">is one whom the relevant officials are punishing.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.116" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T17:36:26.412+09:00">What as a leader you take to be right</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.117" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T03:15:48.947+09:00">is but what the law declares to be wrong.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.118" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T17:37:11.617+09:00">When rewards and punisments, right and wrong</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.119" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T03:18:51.441+09:00">are altogether in a logical mess in every conceivable direction,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.120" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T03:21:15.768+09:00">then even ten Yellow Emperors</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.121" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T17:39:13.012+09:00">are incapable of sorting them out."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.122" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T17:41:35.78+09:00">The King of Qí was lost for words to respond with.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.123" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T03:22:15.325+09:00">Thus I consider that your words have a resemblance with those of the King of Qí.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.124" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-10T17:47:21.266+09:00">You are intelligent enough to raise objections against the thesis that a white horse is not a horse,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.125" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T03:28:17.34+09:00">but you are not intelligent enough to know how to raise objections against that thesis.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.126" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T03:33:10.615+09:00">Explaining it with the last-mentioned example,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.127" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T03:41:39.594+09:00">you are just like the category of people who understand the expression 'being fond of true gentlemen',</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T01:29:22.219+09:00">are inconsistent.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:31:00.124+09:00">Moreover, as for wanting to study with me,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:31:17.49+09:00">this would be because one would consider one's intellectual prowess and learning not to reach mine.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T01:38:07.031+09:00">this is first to teach someone and thereafter to go on to take that person as one's teacher.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T01:38:59.669+09:00">that is (logically) unacceptable.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-11T23:35:49.045+09:00">is like the way the King of Qí addressed Yīn Wén.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0941_CHANT_001-4a.128" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2020-04-12T03:41:18.885+09:00">but who are not intelligent enough to investigate and come to a clear understanding of true gentlemen."</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
